\begin_inset Formula $\uu^*,\uu^{n+1}$
\end_inset

 involves two right-hand-side evaluations and linear solver executions. Therefore, each HIRK updating is counted as 
\begin_inset Formula $2.0$
\end_inset

 effective iterations. Although one could calibrate the coefficients using theoretical analyses or empirical data to get a more precise measurement of consumption, the current simple coefficients for effective iterations are found to be sufficient.
